By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – The Senate President, Ahmad Lawan, has sent his condolences to Senator Teslim Folarin, over the death of his wife, Barrister Angela Nwaka Folarin. Lawan expresses shock and deep sadness at the tragic news, describing the deceased as a pillar of the family. The Special Adviser (Media) to President of the Senate, Ola Awoniyi who disclosed this in a statement on Saturday quoted the Senate President as saying: “I commiserate with Distinguished Senator Folarin on this most painful experience of the death of a loving wife. “We believe that any occurrence like this, as devout Muslims, is the will of Allah but I pray the Almighty God to comfort the family,” Lawan says. The Senate President condoled with members of the Folarin family, the Government and people of Oyo State over the painful loss and prayed Allah to forgive the shortcomings of the dear departed and accept her soul into Aljannah firdausi. Sundiata Post recalls that Senator Folarin is a federal Lawmaker representing Oyo Central Senatorial District in the 9th senate.  By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - President of the Senate, Ahmad Lawan, has grieved over the death of former Senator, Gbenga Aluko, who died at the weekend. Lawan who sent his condolences to the family of the late Aluko also commiserated with the Government and people of Ekiti State… In "News" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - The President of the Senate, Ahmad Lawan, has sent his condolences to the Dangote family over the demise of Alhaji Sani Dangote, the Vice President of the Dangote Group. Lawan says the death of Sani Dangote is a great loss to Nigeria and… In "News" By Chibuike Nwabuko  Abuja – (Sundiata Post) -   President of the Senate, Ahmad Lawan, has expressed grief over the demise of former Oyo State Governor, Abiola Ajimobi. Lawan reinded that late Senator Ajimobi served with merit at the upper legislative chamber between 2003 and 2007 during which time he was… In "News"